content.description:
This is a fun moving little flared-tight-hands and fingers splitter somewhat reminiscent of the crux of

Hypertension

.  At the horizontal, traverse right on easier ground to top out.
content.protection: Fingers-sized gear for the crack, there are lots of options for the anchor.  Walk off.
content.location: This is on the far rightmost part of Coyote Rocks if looking from the parking area at the end of the road.  To get there, head more or less north from the parking lot for a hundred yards or so, at which point you should run right into a small outcrop of rock.  This crack is the straight up splitter on the right side of the wall.
